  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Defendant Cory L Gransberry in court with Attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Grant Scaife appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Sonderhouse makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE:  $719.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid at $75.00 per month, commencing 7/15/16, alternate 18 days jail if not paid)

**Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**
